# Using Scope

Scope is a local-first kanban for projects, epics, stories, and bugs. It ships
as a CLI, a GitHub-Projects-style web UI, and a Model Context Protocol server.

## When to use

- Multi-step task ("rebuild auth", "ship feature X") → create an epic plus child stories.
- Starting a session → list open tickets in the project for context.
- Finishing a piece of work → mark the ticket `done`, attach the branch / PR.
- Discovering a real bug → create a `bug` ticket with reproduction steps.

Skip Scope for one-off questions or trivial single-edit requests.

## How to access

If MCP is connected, `mcp__scope__*` tools cover everything. Otherwise:

```bash
scope --json ticket list -p MA
scope --json ticket show MA-3
```

Install if needed: `brew install briannadoubt/tap/scope`

## Data model

| | |
|---|---|
| Project | top-level container, has a 2-10 letter key (`MA`) |
| Epic | high-level body of work, parent for stories/bugs |
| Story | unit of work toward an epic |
| Bug | defect, can live under an epic |
| Status | `backlog` → `todo` → `in_progress` → `in_review` → `done` (+ `cancelled`) |
| Priority | `low` / `medium` / `high` / `urgent` |
| Relations | `blocks`, `blocked_by`, `relates_to`, `duplicates`, `duplicate_of` |

## Common operations

```bash
scope init
scope project create my-app MA "My App"

scope ticket create MA "Auth refactor" -t epic -p high
scope ticket create MA "OAuth login"  -t story --parent MA-1

scope branch  MA-2 feat/oauth --in-progress
scope pr      MA-2 https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/42 --in-review
scope status  MA-2 done

scope board -p MA
scope --json ticket show MA-2
scope comment MA-2 "Token expiry was 5min; bumped to 1h" --by cursor
scope link add MA-2 blocked_by MA-7
```

## Guardrails

- Don't create projects without explicit user request.
- Don't delete tickets — set status to `cancelled` instead.
- Keep titles human-readable; implementation details go in the description.
- Update status as work happens, not all at once at the end.
- Use `--by <name>` so the history shows who touched what.

## Realtime + multi-agent

`scope serve` runs the UI and the HTTP MCP endpoint in one process. Writes
push to all viewers via SSE in ~100ms. With multiple agents, **read state
before writing state** — last write wins on conflicting updates.

